external_knowledge:
Above-average projected fantasy points: refers to projected fantasy points greater than the average projected fantasy points across the league; 
Uninjured players: Players with no recorded injury (injury_id is NULL);
Weighted on-base average (wOBA): a sabermetric measure of a player's overall batting ability, weighted by the type of hit;
Projected fantasy points (FP): a prediction of a player's fantasy score in a game, which is based on their performance and other factors.
